halfway house
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:hotel (orig. cf OED halfway to one's destination, and so a convenient stopping-place); in NZ, a coaching term which is still extant in this extended use for a `country pub' among very old people (ca1947-8 at least).
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
